definition.value: A D-altropyranose in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has alpha configuration.
Any carboxylic acid carrying an unspecified halogen substituent at the 2R-position.
A deoxytalose that is alpha-D-talopyranose in which the hydroxy goroup at position 6 has been replaced by a hydrogen.
A D-idopyranose in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has beta configuration.
A beta-D-Glcp-(1->6)-D-Galp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has beta configuration.
